Reasoning: The paper deals with information theory and its applications in common information extraction and private sources synthesis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves machine learning techniques and correlation analysis, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia) likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the optimization problems, which can be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
